item.title: These Logos
item.description: Where did the logos came from? http://fontawesome.io/icons/ Font Awesome is fully open source and is GPL friendly. You can use it for commercial projects, open source projects, or really just about whatever you want. Attribution is no longer required as of Font Awesome 3.0 but is much appreciated: “Font Awesome by Dave Gandy - http://fontawesome.io". Font License Applies to all desktop and webfont files in the following directory: font-awesome/fonts/.
